<1ST_LINE>r a AM-BRF--Break-inNote     08-21 0145</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Break-in Note,0149</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Intruder Calls Optometrist `Dumb' For Leaving Door Unlocked</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Someone broke into and ransacked an
optometrist's office, then left a note chiding the eye doctor for
being short-sighted and leaving the door unlocked, police said
Sunday.
   ``You're pretty dumb to leave your back door open. Please in the
future, don't leave it open,'' the handwritten note said. ``In a
world like today's, you can't trust anyone. So don't be dumb.''
   The Panorama City office was ransacked between 5 p.m. Saturday
and 7 a.m. Sunday, when a janitor discovered the break-in, Sgt.
Jeff Sheldon said.
   Some pairs of glasses were thrown around the office, and someone
had drawn on posters with felt-tip markers, he said.
   Police didn't yet know if anything had been stolen.
   The address of the office was not released because the
proprietor had not been notified.
</TEXT>
